{
  "text": "Sexual risk behaviors in the past month (frequency of condom use during vaginal and anal sex with male clients ['infrequent' was defined as using condoms never or sometimes vs. always] and self-efficacy towards condom use (4-point Likert scale responses [dichotomized into strongly agree/agree and strongly disagree/disagree] regarding the ability to use condoms: properly, each time one has sex, while under the influence of drugs or alcohol, without any instruction, and whether one can have condoms available each time they have sex) [CITATION_1] .",
